        <!-- Section 1: WAI (Web Accessibility Initiative) -->
        <section class="content">
            <h2>5.1 WAI (Web Accessibility Initiative)</h2>
            <h3>Who</h3>
            <p>Led by the W3C, the WAI works to improve web accessibility for people with disabilities.</p>

            <h3>What</h3>
            <p>WAI provides guidelines like the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) to ensure that websites are accessible. Explore the guidelines on the <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/standards-guidelines/wcag/" target="_blank">W3C WAI Website</a>.</p>

            <div class="example">
                <h4>Example:</h4>
                <p>Using <code>alt</code> attributes for images: <code>&lt;img src="example.jpg" alt="Description of the image"&gt;</code></p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: Section 508 (U.S.) -->
        <section class="content">
            <h2>5.2 Section 508 (U.S.)</h2>
            <h3>What</h3>
            <p>A U.S. law requiring federal websites to be accessible to all citizens. Learn more about Section 508 at the <a href="https://www.section508.gov/" target="_blank">Section 508 Official Site</a>.</p>

            <div class="example">
                <h4>Example:</h4>
                <p>Adding closed captions to a video: <code>&lt;video controls&gt;&lt;track src="captions.vtt" kind="captions" srclang="en" label="English"&gt;&lt;/video&gt;</code></p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

